Internet Sculptures is a small brand that designs, produces, and sells interactive sculptures that originate in Spencer Chang’s art practice.
&nbsp;
We focus on combining playful and functional digital experiences with beautiful art objects to create sites of whimsical ritual in a home. Our design philosophy plays with the everyday tasks and small moments that make up our lives, honoring them in a ritual-specific sculpture.
&nbsp;
We're inspired by toys that feel magical (like interactive Gacha items) and functional sculptures (like Isamu Noguchi's Akari & Yoshitomo Nara's clock) to create beautiful objects with playful twists on everyday function.
&nbsp;
- Several sold out drops on independent online store in 1 year of opening
- Featured in the New Museum store, Rhizome.org’s holiday guide, FWB’s Winter Bazaar, among others.
- Over 2M+ views across social platforms
&nbsp;
See al[l Computing-Infused Object experiments](https://spencer.place/creation/computing-infused-objects).
